7. Proposed Construction Workflow

The following conceptual sequence outlines how such a habitat might be constructed. This workflow is presented as a theoretical scenario for analysis purposes; no actual construction activities are proposed or planned.

7.1 Phase 0: Pre-Deployment

Prior to habitat construction, the following infrastructure would be emplaced:

· Power system (40 kWe nuclear fission or equivalent solar array with storage)
· Communications relay
· Landing pad for precision cargo delivery
· Initial ISRU plant for atmospheric processing

7.2 Phase 1: Site Preparation

Estimated duration: 30–60 days (robotic)

1. Land construction robotics suite via dedicated cargo lander.
2. Deploy and commission robotic systems.
3. Survey site and establish local coordinate system.
4. Excavate foundation area to depth of 0.5 m.
5. Compact foundation layer to high relative density.
6. Place leveling layer of fine regolith.

7.3 Phase 2: Outer Shell Construction

Estimated duration: 180–240 days (robotic)

1. Days 1–30: Construct base ring and lower walls to 1 m height.
2. Days 31–90: Continue layered construction with spiral-continuous toolpath.
3. Days 91–150: Construct dome apex, transitioning to overhead deposition.
4. Days 151–210: Complete shell, apply surface sealant if specified.
5. Days 211–240: Quality assurance and thermal cycling tests.

Notional printing parameters:

· Layer height: 5 cm
· Bead width: 10 cm
· Print speed: 0.5 m/min (linear bead deposition)
· Total print time (continuous): ~2,000 hours (83 days)
· With 50% duty cycle: 166 days

7.4 Phase 3: Interior Preparation

Estimated duration: 30–60 days (robotic)

1. Install floor leveling system.
2. Route utility conduits.
3. Place interior support structures.
4. Verify dimensional accuracy for module fit.
5. Clean interior of loose dust.

7.5 Phase 4: Module Deployment

Estimated duration: 14–30 days (robotic with optional human oversight)

1. Land habitat modules on prepared pad adjacent to shell.
2. Transfer modules to shell interior using crane or winch system.
3. Position modules on support points.
4. Connect utilities.
5. Inflate and activate pressure vessels.
6. Perform leak checks and pressurization tests.

7.6 Phase 5: Commissioning

Estimated duration: 30 days (robotic, plus human if present)

1. Activate ECLSS and establish habitable atmosphere.
2. Install interior outfitting.
3. Conduct integrated systems tests.
4. Perform unmanned operational test.
5. Certify habitat for human occupancy.

