Appendix E: Cost Model Derivations and Sensitivity Tables

E.1 Derivation of the Cost Function

The total cost per square meter is:

C_{\text{total}} = C_{\text{energy}} + C_{\text{robotics}} + C_{\text{transport}} + C_{\text{systems}} + C_{\text{amortized}}

Each term is derived as follows:

Energy Cost:

C_{\text{energy}} = m_{\text{regolith}} \cdot e_P \cdot c_E

Robotics Cost:

C_{\text{robotics}} = \frac{M_{\text{robotics}} \cdot c_T}{A_{\text{total}}}

Transport Cost:

C_{\text{transport}} = m_{\text{import}} \cdot c_T

Systems Cost:

C_{\text{systems}} = \text{constant (estimated from ISS data)}

Amortized Development:

C_{\text{amortized}} = \frac{C_{\text{development}}}{A_{\text{total}}}

E.2 Breakeven Analysis

The breakeven area $A_{BE}$ is the constructed area at which total ISRU cost equals total full-import cost:

C_{\text{ISRU}}(A) = C_{\text{full import}}(A)

\frac{M_{\text{ISRU}} \cdot c_T}{A} + C_{\text{energy}} + m_{\text{import}} \cdot c_T + C_{\text{systems}} + \frac{C_{\text{dev}}}{A} = (m_{\text{regolith}} + m_{\text{import}}) \cdot c_T + C_{\text{systems}} + \frac{C_{\text{dev}}}{A}

Simplifying:

\frac{M_{\text{ISRU}} \cdot c_T}{A} + C_{\text{energy}} = m_{\text{regolith}} \cdot c_T

Solving for $A$:

A_{BE} = \frac{M_{\text{ISRU}} \cdot c_T}{m_{\text{regolith}} \cdot c_T - C_{\text{energy}}}

With baseline values:

A_{BE} = \frac{4,300 \cdot 100,000}{3,000 \cdot 100,000 - 600} = \frac{430 \times 10^6}{300 \times 10^6 - 600} \approx 1.43 \text{ m²}

